    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-01-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-01-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="409"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d409">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.151/130: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Greece</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacVeagh</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-01-22">January 22,
                            1935</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3. Your 7, January 19, 4 p.m. On the basis of the information now before the
                    Department on this subject, it sees no reason to modify the view expressed in
                    its 59 of November 1, 1932<note n="31" xml:id="d409fn31">Not printed.</note>
                    that no substantial American interest appears to be involved. Under the
                    circumstances intervention by the Legation is not considered warranted.</p>
                <p>For your confidential information the Department considers untenable the
                    contention that Ulen and Company can be held responsible under Article 44 of the
                    contract for compulsory delivery of waterworks funds to Greek Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
